Calculated Columns

These will help create better slicers and visuals:

1️⃣ BMI Category

BMI Category = 
SWITCH(
    TRUE(),
    'Table'[BMI] < 18.5, "Underweight",
    'Table'[BMI] >= 18.5 && 'Table'[BMI] < 25, "Normal",
    'Table'[BMI] >= 25 && 'Table'[BMI] < 30, "Overweight",
    'Table'[BMI] >= 30, "Obese"
)


Lets you slice data by WHO BMI classification.

2️⃣ Cholesterol Category

Cholesterol Category = 
SWITCH(
    TRUE(),
    'Table'[cholestrol] < 5.2, "Desirable",
    'Table'[cholestrol] >= 5.2 && 'Table'[cholestrol] < 6.2, "Borderline High",
    'Table'[cholestrol] >= 6.2, "High"
)


Gives a quick medical classification for cholesterol.

3️⃣ High Risk Flag

High Risk = 
IF(
    'Table'[Glycated_Hemoglobin] > 6.5 || 
    'Table'[BMI] >= 30 || 
    'Table'[cholestrol] >= 6.2,
    "High Risk",
    "Low/Moderate Risk"
)


Helps filter patients who have multiple high-risk indicators.

Measures

These will be handy for KPI cards and comparative visuals:

1️⃣ Average BMI

Average BMI = AVERAGE('Table'[BMI])


2️⃣ Average Glucose (Glycated Hemoglobin)

Avg HbA1c = AVERAGE('Table'[Glycated_Hemoglobin])


3️⃣ % Diabetic

% Diabetic = 
DIVIDE(
    CALCULATE(COUNTROWS('Table'), 'Table'[Result] = "Diabetic"),
    COUNTROWS('Table'),
    0
)


4️⃣ Average Cholesterol by Outcome

Avg Cholesterol = AVERAGE('Table'[cholestrol])
